    "Name": "Mercury",
    "Details": "The Mercury debuted for the first time in 2742, intended as a replacement for the aging Wasps and Stingers in use by the Star League Defense Force. Hailed as the beginning of a new age in 'Mech design, the Mercury was faster and better-armed than its competition without sacrificing armor protection. It also featured an advancement in weapons installation, making use of a modular replacement system to allow for considerably faster and easier repairs. The Mercury carries an assortment of energy weapons which helps to extend its endurance on long campaigns. The primary weapons are two Medium Lasers in the right arm and left torso, supported by two Small Lasers in the center torso and head. The heart of the Mercury is its MASC System which, in combination with a 160 fusion engine, allows for momentary bursts of speed up to 172 km/h. Three tons of Ferro-Fibrous armor gives it superior protection compared to other 20-ton 'Mechs.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Modular Weapons</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 0.97</color></b>",
